HOUSE BILL 1629
By Lamberth
SENATE BILL 1885
By Johnson
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Section
15-2-129, relative to songwriters.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 15-2-129, is amended by deleting the
section and substituting instead:
The month of February of each year must be observed as "Tennessee
Songwriters Month" to promote Tennessee's musical heritage by recognizing the
contributions of past and present songwriters to this state.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
